    <title type="html"><![CDATA[How to Execute a Ruby Script in Terminal Using Shebang]]></title>
    <link href="http://andylinid45.github.io/blog/2015/08/22/how-to-execute-a-ruby-script-in-terminal/"/>
    <updated>2015-08-22T12:14:08+08:00</updated>
    <id>http://andylinid45.github.io/blog/2015/08/22/how-to-execute-a-ruby-script-in-terminal</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><code>
sudo apt-get install ruby
</code></p>

<p>which ruby
<code>
/usr/bin/ruby
</code></p>

<p>please the shebang line on the first line of your script
```</p>

<h1>!/usr/bin/ruby -w</h1>

<p>```</p>

<p><code>
chmod +x your_script.rb
./your_script.rb
</code></p>
]]></content>
